# 🧠 Turing-Guided Reinforcement Learning
### Evolving Environments to Improve Agent Learning

---

## 🚀 Overview

This project explores a different paradigm in reinforcement learning:

> **Instead of making the agent smarter, can we make the environment smarter?**

We combine:
- **Turing reaction-diffusion systems** to generate structured environments  
- **Genetic Algorithms (GA)** to evolve those environments  
- **Reinforcement Learning (RL)** to evaluate agent performance  

The result is a framework where the **environment itself becomes a guidance mechanism** for learning.

---

## 💡 Core Idea

Traditional RL assumes a fixed environment.

This project introduces:

> **Environment Optimization for Learning**

The environment is not static — it is **evolved to help the agent perform better**.

A reaction-diffusion (Turing) system generates spatial patterns that:
- create gradients  
- organize space  
- provide local structure  

These patterns act as a **guidance field** for the agent.

